  "change": {
    "description": "Per-row full-attention context diagnostics now force the paged-spans BF16 context kernel instead of the dense single-row context kernel; this preserves row block-table/live-span addressing when replaying a row after batch KV append. The default c1 path is unchanged unless force_paged_context=True is requested internally by the diagnostic branch.",
    "files": [
      "hipengine/runtime/qwen35_paro.py",
      "tests/test_qwen35_decode_state.py"
    ]
  },
  "conclusion": "The c2 per_row_context_only diagnostic blocker is eliminated: before the patch it reproduced [103,137], while after forcing paged-spans row context it is green 3/3 at [137,137] and the final active c2 verify remains 137. This supports the diagnosis that the context-only red signature came from replaying per-row context with the dense single-row context kernel after batch KV append, not from sampler or MoE. The combined per_row_context_gate diagnostic remains red at [103,137], so per-row context+per-row gate is still not a retained fallback. No throughput claim is made.",
